snippet.title: Act of Consecration to the Immaculate Heart of Mary, part 5 of 5
snippet.description:
https://www.stmaron.org/press-releases/solemn-act-of-consecration-of-humanity-and-russia-and-ukraine-in-particular-to-the-immaculate-heart-of-mary

Pope Francis asks us to join in a solemn Act of Consecration of humanity, and Russia and Ukraine in particular, to the Immaculate Heart of Mary. The Holy Father himself will pray his solemn Act of Consecration in Rome at approximately 6:30pm (Rome), 12:30pm (Eastern time), March 25, 2022.

He asks us to join him in prayer in our churches, homes and places of prayer that day, Friday, March 25.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Julian.

Eighth prayer -- Dec. 22: (modern)

O King of Great Counsel, you have united the magnificence 
of  your  resplendent  power  with  the  prudence  of  human 
judgment when you, the almighty and powerful God, took 
flight to Egypt to escape Herod. We implore you, through 
your  pure  nativity  and  through  the  intercession  of  your 
mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  grant  us 
sound judgment in all of our actions, that we may act in all 
wisdom and serve you all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Eighth oration -- Dec. 22: (classic)

O King of Great Counsel,
You joined Your admirable power with the prudence of humuan judgment
when You, the Mighty and AII-Powerful God, fled into Egypt from the face of Herod.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us good judgment in all our actions,
that we may think and act wisely all the days of our lives
as we subject ourselves to Your divine service.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joyce.



Third prayer -- Dec. 17 (modern)

O Admirable Leader, you have guided the people to obey 
you, not by harshness but by the tenderness of your love. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen  one,  to  teach  us  perfect  obedience  to  your  holy 
commandments  and  to  our  superiors,  not  for  fear  of 
punishment,  or  constraint,  or  external  force,  but  by  the 
assent  of  our  minds,  the  surrender  of  our  hearts,  the 
enthusiasm of our spirits, and the joy of our souls. Amen.






Third oration -- Dec. 17 (classic)

O Admirable Leader Who gains the obedience of Your people not by the severity of Your judgment
but by the sweetness of Your love and Your welcome sojourn among us.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to teach us complete obedience to Your holy commandments
and to submit to our superiors not for fear of punishment
but by a willing surrender of mind and heart, with gladness of heart and spirit.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Tony.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 18: (modern)

O  Lord,  Wine  of  the  Virgins  and  Lily  of  Purity,  through 
your body all bodies are purified and all souls are clothed 
in chastity. By dwelling in the womb of your mother, you 
have  made  her  the  most  pure  and  glorious  of  all  virgins. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen one, to make our souls and bodies chaste and our 
thoughts and actions pure, that we may serve you all the 
days of our lives. Amen.  



Fourth oration -- Dec. 18: (classic)

0 Wine of Virgins and Lily of Purity,
Who by a touch of Your hand heals the body and cleanses the soul;
Who by dwelling in the womb of Your Mother has made her the purest of the pure and most admirable among virgins;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us to be pure in soul and body and clean in act clean and thought,
that we may serve You with a clean heart and pure body all the days of our lives.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Samantha.

Second oration -- Dec 16:

O Hope of the Patriarchs and longing of the Gentiles,
in Your Nativity You have granted us hope.
The joy of this hope has called together the Shepherds, 
the Magi and all believers in Your Holy Name,
and led them to adore You with all the acclaim of their hearts. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to keep us, by Your grace, from attachment to earthly goods.
Teach us not to depend only on ourselves and the weak ones of this world,
but to rely only on Your Fatherly direction and Your Divine Providence. 
Attract our hearts and minds to reflect on Your heavenly riches 
and to aspire and long for them above.

Amen

snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Nisreen.

Seventh prayer -- Dec. 21: (modern)

O  Lord,  you  are  one  person  who  has  two  natures,  and 
have taught us what you have heard from the Father. We 
implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

Amen

have taught us what you have heard from the Father. We 
implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Christelle.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (modern)
O Mighty One, seated in the heavenly heights,
you left the glory  of  your divinity and loved the lowliness 
of our human nature to become our model of humility and 
lowliness.  We  implore  you,  through  your  pure  nativity 
and  through  the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint 
Joseph, your chosen one, to give us humility of heart and 
the  denial  of  ourselves,  that  we  may  remove  all  pride 
which  prevents  us  from  knowing  you.  We  would  then 
realize the weakness of our condition and glorify you, for 
you  alone  are  holy  and  great  is  your  name.  To  you  be 
glory, power, and strength. Amen.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (classic)

O Most High, by nature supreme and outranking all men and all things,
Who has left the magnificence of Your Divinity
and loved the lowliness of our humanity to become for us a
model in humility and lowliness;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us humility of heart and an accurate estimation of ourselves.
Help us to conquer every show of false pride, which would have us choose
our own whims rather than Your Will.
May we realize that, compared to You, we are little indeed.
Glory be to You, for You alone are holy and great is Your Name.
To You be Glory, Magnificence and Power!

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joyce.



Third prayer -- Dec. 17 (modern)

O Admirable Leader, you have guided the people to obey 
you, not by harshness but by the tenderness of your love. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen  one,  to  teach  us  perfect  obedience  to  your  holy 
commandments  and  to  our  superiors,  not  for  fear  of 
punishment,  or  constraint,  or  external  force,  but  by  the 
assent  of  our  minds,  the  surrender  of  our  hearts,  the 
enthusiasm of our spirits, and the joy of our souls. Amen.






Third oration -- Dec. 17 (classic)

O Admirable Leader Who gains the obedience of Your people not by the severity of Your judgment
but by the sweetness of Your love and Your welcome sojourn among us.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to teach us complete obedience to Your holy commandments
and to submit to our superiors not for fear of punishment
but by a willing surrender of mind and heart, with gladness of heart and spirit.

Amen

snippet.title: The Genealogy of Jesus
snippet.description:
December 20, 2020: The Genealogy of Jesus.
Today's Divine Liturgy can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/sunday.pdf and the novena at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.

Page 66 -- The Genealogy of Jesus
Page 748 -- Creed
Page 754 -- Anaphora of the Twelve Apostles

We will pray Christmas Novena, (sixth day, Dec. 20) after the Divine Litugry.   The text can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf

This week's bulletin can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/201220-bulletin.pdf



Sixth Prayer of the Christmas Novena: (modern text)

O Word of God, you have come from the mouth of God to 
be the life for all people. You became the living bread and 
were born in Bethlehem, “the House of Bread”, to satisfy 
our  hunger.  We  implore  you,  through  your  pure  nativity 
and  through  the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint 
Joseph, your chosen one, to grant us an insatiable hunger 
for  your  pure  Body  and  Blood.    May  we  approach  your 
altars  and  with  proper  preparation receive your Sacred 
Mysteries for our salvation and eternal life. Amen.




Sixth Oration of the Christmas Novena: (classic text)

O Word of God, Who comes from the Mouth of God to be the  Life of all men;
You Who became Living Bread and was born in Bethlehem, "The House of Bread",
to satisfy our hunger.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us a piercing hunger for that Bread which is Your Pure Body and Blood.
May we ever approach Your altar and receive Your Sacred Mysteries
with fitting preparation so that our Communion may be for us salvation and life everlasting.

Amen.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Christelle.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 18: (modern)

O  Lord,  Wine  of  the  Virgins  and  Lily  of  Purity,  through 
your body all bodies are purified and all souls are clothed 
in chastity. By dwelling in the womb of your mother, you 
have  made  her  the  most  pure  and  glorious  of  all  virgins. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen one, to make our souls and bodies chaste and our 
thoughts and actions pure, that we may serve you all the 
days of our lives. Amen.  



Fourth oration -- Dec. 18: (classic)

0 Wine of Virgins and Lily of Purity,
Who by a touch of Your hand heals the body and cleanses the soul;
Who by dwelling in the womb of Your Mother has made her the purest of the pure and most admirable among virgins;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us to be pure in soul and body and clean in act clean and thought,
that we may serve You with a clean heart and pure body all the days of our lives.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by George.

Ninth prayer -- Dec. 23: (modern)

O  Lord,  though  you  are  rich  by  nature,  you  loved  the 
poverty  of  our  humanity  when  you  became  man  like  us. 
Though you were the descendant of kings and the heir of 
David, the venerable, you were satisfied with a grotto and 
a  humble  manger.    We  implore  you,  through  your  pure 
nativity and through the intercession of your mother and 
Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  give  us  a  love  of 
voluntary  poverty,  that  we  may  be  satisfied  only  with 
what  is  necessary  for  our  existence,  avoiding  waste  and 
the love of an easy life, all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Ninth Oration -- Dec. 23: (classic)

0 God, Who in Your very nature contain all the riches of heaven and earth,
You loved the poverty of humanity by choosing to become one of us,
You are the descendant of Kings and the Heir of David the Venerable.
You were satisfied to be born a stable and a humble manger.
 
We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity 
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us an appreciation of voluntary poverty.
May we be satisfied with only that which is necessary for the maintenance of our lives.
Teach us to flee from excessive luxury and the love of abundance all the days of our lives.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joseph.

First oration -- Dec. 15:

O Beautiful One in splendor,
fairer than the children of this world, 
in Your inexplicable love for us, You became a man
to show us the invisible beauty of Your Divinity
in the splendor of Your visible body,
which You have taken from the Virgin Mary.
By this, You have attracted us to Your Divine Love,
You, Beloved of the Father and Only Delight of His Heart. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to enkindle Your love in our hearts
and enlighten our minds with the rays of Your heavenly grace,
that we may love You with our whole heart and mind.
May we love everyone in You and for You, 
You, Who alone are worthy of the love of all hearts,

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Tony.

Eighth prayer -- Dec. 22: (modern)

O King of Great Counsel, you have united the magnificence 
of  your  resplendent  power  with  the  prudence  of  human 
judgment when you, the almighty and powerful God, took 
flight to Egypt to escape Herod. We implore you, through 
your  pure  nativity  and  through  the  intercession  of  your 
mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  grant  us 
sound judgment in all of our actions, that we may act in all 
wisdom and serve you all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Eighth oration -- Dec. 22: (classic)

O King of Great Counsel,
You joined Your admirable power with the prudence of human judgment
when You, the Mighty and AII-Powerful God, fled into Egypt from the face of Herod.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us good judgment in all our actions,
that we may think and act wisely all the days of our lives
as we subject ourselves to Your divine service.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Julian.

Eighth prayer -- Dec. 22: (modern)

O King of Great Counsel, you have united the magnificence 
of  your  resplendent  power  with  the  prudence  of  human 
judgment when you, the almighty and powerful God, took 
flight to Egypt to escape Herod. We implore you, through 
your  pure  nativity  and  through  the  intercession  of  your 
mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  grant  us 
sound judgment in all of our actions, that we may act in all 
wisdom and serve you all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Eighth oration -- Dec. 22: (classic)

O King of Great Counsel,
You joined Your admirable power with the prudence of humuan judgment
when You, the Mighty and AII-Powerful God, fled into Egypt from the face of Herod.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us good judgment in all our actions,
that we may think and act wisely all the days of our lives
as we subject ourselves to Your divine service.

Amen

https://www.stmaron.org/press-releases/solemn-act-of-consecration-of-humanity-and-russia-and-ukraine-in-particular-to-the-immaculate-heart-of-mary

Pope Francis asks us to join in a solemn Act of Consecration of humanity, and Russia and Ukraine in particular, to the Immaculate Heart of Mary. The Holy Father himself will pray his solemn Act of Consecration in Rome at approximately 6:30pm (Rome), 12:30pm (Eastern time), March 25, 2022.

He asks us to join him in prayer in our churches, homes and places of prayer that day, Friday, March 25.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Marielle.

Second oration -- Dec 16:

O Hope of the Patriarchs and longing of the Gentiles,
in Your Nativity You have granted us hope.
The joy of this hope has called together the Shepherds, 
the Magi and all believers in Your Holy Name,
and led them to adore You with all the acclaim of their hearts. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to keep us, by Your grace, from attachment to earthly goods.
Teach us not to depend only on ourselves and the weak ones of this world,
but to rely only on Your Fatherly direction and Your Divine Providence. 
Attract our hearts and minds to reflect on Your heavenly riches 
and to aspire and long for them above.

Amen

snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.

First oration -- Dec. 15:

O Beautiful One in splendor,
fairer than the children of this world, 
in Your inexplicable love for us, You became a man
to show us the invisible beauty of Your Divinity
in the splendor of Your visible body,
which You have taken from the Virgin Mary.
By this, You have attracted us to Your Divine Love,
You, Beloved of the Father and Only Delight of His Heart. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to enkindle Your love in our hearts
and enlighten our minds with the rays of Your heavenly grace,
that we may love You with our whole heart and mind.
May we love everyone in You and for You, 
You, Who alone are worthy of the love of all hearts,

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Caroline.

Seventh prayer -- Dec. 21: (modern)

O  Lord,  you  are  one  person  who  has  two  natures,  and 
have taught us what you have heard from the Father. We 
implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

Amen

snippet.title: Private service
snippet.description:
Dear Parishioners & Friends,

We received the sad news of the passing of Fortunée Lutfi to eternal life. She is the widow of Bahjat Lutfi, the mother of Edouard, Najib, Rita, Leila, Haifa, Shouly and Jacqueline (deceased). Her sisters are Linda Shouela and Susan Hadriye and her deceased brothers are Joseph, Isaac, Albert and Gaby Mizrahi.

Visiting hours will be held at Our Lady of Lebanon Cathedral (113 Remsen Street, Brooklyn, NY 11201) on Sunday, May 5th, from  3 to 7 pm followed by the Prayer of Incense and a mercy meal.

The Funeral Divine Liturgy will be held the next day at 10 am at Our Lady of Lebanon Cathedral (113 Remsen St., Brooklyn, NY 11201) followed by the burial at Forest Green Park Cemetery (535 Texas Rd., Morganville, NJ 07551)


May a choir of angels accompany Fortunée to the heavenly abode with the righteous and just.

Abouna Dominique Hanna
Our Lady of Lebanon Maronite Cathedral 

Brooklyn, NY


“By his death, Christ preserved us from corruption, and by his resurrection he renewed our image and granted us eternal life in his kingdom.” ­The Book of Offering

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Julian.

Eighth prayer -- Dec. 22: (modern)

O King of Great Counsel, you have united the magnificence 
of  your  resplendent  power  with  the  prudence  of  human 
judgment when you, the almighty and powerful God, took 
flight to Egypt to escape Herod. We implore you, through 
your  pure  nativity  and  through  the  intercession  of  your 
mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  grant  us 
sound judgment in all of our actions, that we may act in all 
wisdom and serve you all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Eighth oration -- Dec. 22: (classic)

O King of Great Counsel,
You joined Your admirable power with the prudence of humuan judgment
when You, the Mighty and AII-Powerful God, fled into Egypt from the face of Herod.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us good judgment in all our actions,
that we may think and act wisely all the days of our lives
as we subject ourselves to Your divine service.

Amen

Sixth oration -- Dec. 20: (classic)

O Word of God, Who comes
from the Mouth of God to be the
Life of all men; You Who became
Living Bread and was born in
Bethlehem, "The House of Bread",
to satisfy our hunger; We beseech
You, through Your Pure Nativity
and the intercession of Your
Mother and Saint Joseph, Your
Chosen One, to grant us a piercing
hunger for that Bread which is
Your Pure Body and Blood.  May
we ever approach Your altar and
receive Your Sacred Mysteries
with fitting preparation so that our
Communion may be for us
salvation and life everlasting.
Amen.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Christelle.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (modern)
O Mighty One, seated in the heavenly heights,
you left the glory  of  your divinity and loved the lowliness 
of our human nature to become our model of humility and 
lowliness.  We  implore  you,  through  your  pure  nativity 
and  through  the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint 
Joseph, your chosen one, to give us humility of heart and 
the  denial  of  ourselves,  that  we  may  remove  all  pride 
which  prevents  us  from  knowing  you.  We  would  then 
realize the weakness of our condition and glorify you, for 
you  alone  are  holy  and  great  is  your  name.  To  you  be 
glory, power, and strength. Amen.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (classic)

O Most High, by nature supreme and outranking all men and all things,
Who has left the magnificence of Your Divinity
and loved the lowliness of our humanity to become for us a
model in humility and lowliness;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us humility of heart and an accurate estimation of ourselves.
Help us to conquer every show of false pride, which would have us choose
our own whims rather than Your Will.
May we realize that, compared to You, we are little indeed.
Glory be to You, for You alone are holy and great is Your Name.
To You be Glory, Magnificence and Power!

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Nisreen.

Seventh prayer -- Dec. 21: (modern)

O  Lord,  you  are  one  person  who  has  two  natures,  and 
have taught us what you have heard from the Father. We 
implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by William

Ninth prayer -- Dec. 23: (modern)

O  Lord,  though  you  are  rich  by  nature,  you  loved  the 
poverty  of  our  humanity  when  you  became  man  like  us. 
Though you were the descendent of kings and the heir of 
David, the venerable, you were satisfied with a grotto and 
a  humble  manger.    We  implore  you,  through  your  pure 
nativity and through the intercession of your mother and 
Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  give  us  a  love  of 
voluntary  poverty,  that  we  may  be  satisfied  only  with 
what  is  necessary  for  our  existence,  avoiding  waste  and 
the love of an easy life, all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Ninth Oration -- Dec. 23: (classic)

0 God, Who in Your very nature contain all the riches of heaven and earth,
You loved the poverty of humanity by choosing to become one of us,
You are the descendant of Kings and the Heir of David the Venerable.
You were satisfied to be born a stable and a humble manger.
 
We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity 
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us an appreciation of voluntary poverty.
May we be satisfied with only that which is necessary for the maintenance of our lives.
Teach us to flee from excessive luxury and the love of abundance all the days of our lives.

Amen

Sixth oration -- Dec. 20: (classic)

O Word of God, Who comes
from the Mouth of God to be the
Life of all men; You Who became
Living Bread and was born in
Bethlehem, "The House of Bread",
to satisfy our hunger; We beseech
You, through Your Pure Nativity
and the intercession of Your
Mother and Saint Joseph, Your
Chosen One, to grant us a piercing
hunger for that Bread which is
Your Pure Body and Blood.  May
we ever approach Your altar and
receive Your Sacred Mysteries
with fitting preparation so that our
Communion may be for us
salvation and life everlasting.
Amen.

snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joyce.

Third prayer – Dec. 17 (modern)

O Admirable Leader, you have guided the people to obey 
you, not by harshness but by the tenderness of your love. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen  one,  to  teach  us  perfect  obedience  to  your  holy 
commandments  and  to  our  superiors,  not  for  fear  of 
punishment,  or  constraint,  or  external  force,  but  by  the 
assent  of  our  minds,  the  surrender  of  our  hearts,  the 
enthusiasm of our spirits, and the joy of our souls. Amen.

Third oration – Dec. 17 (classic)

O Admirable Leader Who gains the obedience of Your people not by the severity of Your judgment but by the sweetness of Your love and Your welcome sojourn among us.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Tony.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (modern)
O Mighty One, seated in the heavenly heights,
you left the glory  of  your divinity and loved the lowliness 
of our human nature to become our model of humility and 
lowliness.  We  implore  you,  through  your  pure  nativity 
and  through  the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint 
Joseph, your chosen one, to give us humility of heart and 
the  denial  of  ourselves,  that  we  may  remove  all  pride 
which  prevents  us  from  knowing  you.  We  would  then 
realize the weakness of our condition and glorify you, for 
you  alone  are  holy  and  great  is  your  name.  To  you  be 
glory, power, and strength. Amen.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 19: (classic)

O Most High, by nature supreme and outranking all men and all things,
Who has left the magnificence of Your Divinity
and loved the lowliness of our humanity to become for us a
model in humility and lowliness;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us humility of heart and an accurate estimation of ourselves.
Help us to conquer every show of false pride, which would have us choose
our own whims rather than Your Will.
May we realize that, compared to You, we are little indeed.
Glory be to You, for You alone are holy and great is Your Name.
To You be Glory, Magnificence and Power!

Amen

snippet.description:

Cover art by Marielle.

Second oration -- Dec 16:

O Hope of the Patriarchs and longing of the Gentiles,
in Your Nativity You have granted us hope.
The joy of this hope has called together the Shepherds, 
the Magi and all believers in Your Holy Name,
and led them to adore You with all the acclaim of their hearts. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to keep us, by Your grace, from attachment to earthly goods.
Teach us not to depend only on ourselves and the weak ones of this world,
but to rely only on Your Fatherly direction and Your Divine Providence. 
Attract our hearts and minds to reflect on Your heavenly riches 
and to aspire and long for them above.

Amen

implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Christelle.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 18: (modern)

O  Lord,  Wine  of  the  Virgins  and  Lily  of  Purity,  through 
your body all bodies are purified and all souls are clothed 
in chastity. By dwelling in the womb of your mother, you 
have  made  her  the  most  pure  and  glorious  of  all  virgins. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen one, to make our souls and bodies chaste and our 
thoughts and actions pure, that we may serve you all the 
days of our lives. Amen.  



Fourth oration -- Dec. 18: (classic)

0 Wine of Virgins and Lily of Purity,
Who by a touch of Your hand heals the body and cleanses the soul;
Who by dwelling in the womb of Your Mother has made her the purest of the pure and most admirable among virgins;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us to be pure in soul and body and clean in act clean and thought,
that we may serve You with a clean heart and pure body all the days of our lives.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by George.

Ninth prayer -- Dec. 23: (modern)

O  Lord,  though  you  are  rich  by  nature,  you  loved  the 
poverty  of  our  humanity  when  you  became  man  like  us. 
Though you were the descendant of kings and the heir of 
David, the venerable, you were satisfied with a grotto and 
a  humble  manger.    We  implore  you,  through  your  pure 
nativity and through the intercession of your mother and 
Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  give  us  a  love  of 
voluntary  poverty,  that  we  may  be  satisfied  only  with 
what  is  necessary  for  our  existence,  avoiding  waste  and 
the love of an easy life, all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Ninth Oration -- Dec. 23: (classic)

0 God, Who in Your very nature contain all the riches of heaven and earth,
You loved the poverty of humanity by choosing to become one of us,
You are the descendant of Kings and the Heir of David the Venerable.
You were satisfied to be born a stable and a humble manger.
 
We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity 
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us an appreciation of voluntary poverty.
May we be satisfied with only that which is necessary for the maintenance of our lives.
Teach us to flee from excessive luxury and the love of abundance all the days of our lives.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Marielle.

Second oration -- Dec 16:

O Hope of the Patriarchs and longing of the Gentiles,
in Your Nativity You have granted us hope.
The joy of this hope has called together the Shepherds, 
the Magi and all believers in Your Holy Name,
and led them to adore You with all the acclaim of their hearts. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to keep us, by Your grace, from attachment to earthly goods.
Teach us not to depend only on ourselves and the weak ones of this world,
but to rely only on Your Fatherly direction and Your Divine Providence. 
Attract our hearts and minds to reflect on Your heavenly riches 
and to aspire and long for them above.

Amen

snippet.title: The Finding of the Lord in the Temple
snippet.description:
January 5, 2025: The Finding of the Lord in the Temple
Today's Divine Liturgy can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/sunday.pdf.

Page 87 -- The Finding of Our Lord in the Temple
Page 748 -- Creed
Page 815 -- Anaphora of Saint John the Apostle

-----
The Jubilee Prayer

Father in heaven, may the faith you have given us
in your son, Jesus Christ, our brother,
and the flame of charity enkindled
in our hearts by the Holy Spirit,
reawaken in us the blessed hope 
for the coming of your Kingdom.

May your grace transform us
into tireless cultivators of the seeds of the Gospel.
May those seeds transform from within both humanity
and the whole cosmos in the sure expectation
of a new heaven and a new earth,
when, with the powers of Evil vanquished,
your glory will shine eternally.

May the grace of the Jubilee
reawaken in us, Pilgrims of Hope,
a yearning for the treasures of heaven.
May that same grace spread the joy
and peace of our Redeemer throughout the earth.
To you our God, eternally blessed, 
be glory and praise for ever.  Amen

-----

صلاة اليوبيل

أيها الآب الذي في السماوات،
إن الإيمان الذي وهبتَه لنا
بابنك يسوع المسيح، أخانا،
وشعلة المحبة
المُنسكِبَة في قلوبنا بروحك القدوس،
يوقظان فينا الرجاء المبارك لمجيء ملكوتك.
 

إنّ نعمتك تحوّلنا إلى مزارعين مجتهدين للبذور الإنجيلية
التي تُخَمِّر الإنسانية والعالم،
في الانتظار الوثيق
للسماوات الجديدة والأرض الجديدة،
عندما تُهزَم قوى الشر
ويَظهَرُ مجدُك إلى الأبد.

 إنّ نعمة اليوبيل تحيي فينا
نحن، حجاج الرجاء،
الشوق نحو الخيرات السماوية
وتسكب على العالم أجمع
فرح وسلام فادينا.
أيها الإله الأزليّ المبارك،
لك الحمد والتسبيح إلى الأبد، آمين.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Matthew.

Fifth prayer -- Dec. 19: (modern)

O Mighty One, seated in the heavenly heights, you left the 
glory  of  your  divinity  and  loved  the  lowliness  of  our 
human  nature  to  become  our  model  of  humility  and 
lowliness.  We  implore  you,  through  your  pure  nativity 
and  through  the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint 
Joseph, your chosen one, to give us humility of heart and 
the  denial  of  ourselves,  that  we  may  remove  all  pride 
which  prevents  us  from  knowing  you.  We  would  then 
realize the weakness of our condition and glorify you, for 
you  alone  are  holy  and  great  is  your  name.  To  you  be 
glory, power, and strength. Amen.  


Fifth oration -- Dec. 19: (classic)

O Most High, by nature supreme and outranking all men and all things,
Who has left the magnificence of Your Divinity
and loved the lowliness of our humanity
to become for us a model in humility and lowliness;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us humility of heart and an accurate estimation of ourselves.
Help us to conquer every show of false pride,
which would have us choose our own whims rather than Your Will. 
May we realize that, compared to You, we are little indeed.

Glory be to You, for You alone are holy and great is Your Name.
To You be Glory, Magnificence and Power!

Amen

glory, power, and strength. Amen.  


Fifth oration -- Dec. 19: (classic)

O Most High, by nature supreme and outranking all men and all things,
Who has left the magnificence of Your Divinity
and loved the lowliness of our humanity
to become for us a model in humility and lowliness;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us humility of heart and an accurate estimation of ourselves.
Help us to conquer every show of false pride,
which would have us choose our own whims rather than Your Will. 
May we realize that, compared to You, we are little indeed.

Glory be to You, for You alone are holy and great is Your Name.
To You be Glory, Magnificence and Power!

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.

First oration -- Dec. 15:

O Beautiful One in splendor,
fairer than the children of this world, 
in Your inexplicable love for us, You became a man
to show us the invisible beauty of Your Divinity
in the splendor of Your visible body,
which You have taken from the Virgin Mary.
By this, You have attracted us to Your Divine Love,
You, Beloved of the Father and Only Delight of His Heart. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to enkindle Your love in our hearts
and enlighten our minds with the rays of Your heavenly grace,
that we may love You with our whole heart and mind.
May we love everyone in You and for You, 
You, Who alone are worthy of the love of all hearts,

Amen

snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Caroline.

Seventh prayer -- Dec. 21: (modern)

O  Lord,  you  are  one  person  who  has  two  natures,  and 
have taught us what you have heard from the Father. We 
implore you, through your pure nativity and through the 
intercession of your Mother and Saint Joseph, your chosen 
one,  to  grant  us  a  living  faith  and  good  works  in 
accordance  with  that  faith.  Do  not  permit  us  to  lose  the 
reward of our faith because of our wrong doings, but may 
we bear the fruits of true faith and good works. Amen.


Seventh oration -- Dec. 21: (classic)

0 You Who are One person but also have the Nature of man
You Who have told us what You have heard from the Father; 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity and the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One
to grant us an ardent belief in Your teachings and good acts to harmonize with them.
Do not permit us to lose the reward of our faith because of our own wrong doings.
Rather, make our lives fruitful in beliefs and good works.

snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Julian.

Eighth prayer -- Dec. 22: (modern)

O King of Great Counsel, you have united the magnificence 
of  your  resplendent  power  with  the  prudence  of  human 
judgment when you, the almighty and powerful God, took 
flight to Egypt to escape Herod. We implore you, through 
your  pure  nativity  and  through  the  intercession  of  your 
mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your  chosen  one,  to  grant  us 
sound judgment in all of our actions, that we may act in all 
wisdom and serve you all the days of our lives. Amen.  



Eighth oration -- Dec. 22: (classic)

O King of Great Counsel,
You joined Your admirable power with the prudence of humuan judgment
when You, the Mighty and AII-Powerful God, fled into Egypt from the face of Herod.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One, 
to grant us good judgment in all our actions,
that we may think and act wisely all the days of our lives
as we subject ourselves to Your divine service.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joyce.



Third prayer -- Dec. 17 (modern)

O Admirable Leader, you have guided the people to obey 
you, not by harshness but by the tenderness of your love. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  Mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen  one,  to  teach  us  perfect  obedience  to  your  holy 
commandments  and  to  our  superiors,  not  for  fear  of 
punishment,  or  constraint,  or  external  force,  but  by  the 
assent  of  our  minds,  the  surrender  of  our  hearts,  the 
enthusiasm of our spirits, and the joy of our souls. Amen.






Third oration -- Dec. 17 (classic)

O Admirable Leader Who gains the obedience of Your people not by the severity of Your judgment
but by the sweetness of Your love and Your welcome sojourn among us.

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to teach us complete obedience to Your holy commandments
and to submit to our superiors not for fear of punishment
but by a willing surrender of mind and heart, with gladness of heart and spirit.

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Joseph.

First oration -- Dec. 15:

O Beautiful One in splendor,
fairer than the children of this world, 
in Your inexplicable love for us, You became a man
to show us the invisible beauty of Your Divinity
in the splendor of Your visible body,
which You have taken from the Virgin Mary.
By this, You have attracted us to Your Divine Love,
You, Beloved of the Father and Only Delight of His Heart. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to enkindle Your love in our hearts
and enlighten our minds with the rays of Your heavenly grace,
that we may love You with our whole heart and mind.
May we love everyone in You and for You, 
You, Who alone are worthy of the love of all hearts,

Amen

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Tony.

Second oration -- Dec 16:

O Hope of the Patriarchs and longing of the Gentiles,
in Your Nativity You have granted us hope.
The joy of this hope has called together the Shepherds, 
the Magi and all believers in Your Holy Name,
and led them to adore You with all the acclaim of their hearts. 

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Virgin Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to keep us, by Your grace, from attachment to earthly goods.
Teach us not to depend only on ourselves and the weak ones of this world,
but to rely only on Your Fatherly direction and Your Divine Providence. 
Attract our hearts and minds to reflect on Your heavenly riches 
and to aspire and long for them above.

Amen

snippet.title: Prayer Service for Lebanon
snippet.description:
Prayer text: http://ololc.org/doc/prayer-for-lebanon-ramsho.pdf


Brother Bishops. Priests. Deacons and Subdeacons. Consecrated Men and Women. Lay Faithful: 

On  behalf of Archbishop  Anoushavan Tanielian.  President  of CAMECT.  Metropolitan  Joseph
and I invite you to an ecumenical and interfaith prayer service for Lebanon on Tuesday. August
25. 2020 at 7:00 PM at Our Lady of Lebanon Cathedral located at  113  Remsen Street. Brooklyn. NY  11201.  Your  presence.  and  that  of your  family.  friends  and  congregations  would  be  most welcome.

Lebanon needs and deserves our prayers.  One hundred years ago it was a Christian Patriarch and a  Muslim Mufti  who  insured  that  Lebanon would be  a  welcoming  refuge  for  all.  The National Poet  of  1943   insured  once  again  that  Lebanon  would  be  a  shared  dream  of  the  different communities.  In  the   1980's.  even  during  her  civil  war.  Saint  Pope  John  Paul  II  stated  that
"Lebanon is more than a country. it is a message for East and West".

Today  this vision.  dream. and hope of Lebanon  is  in  need of our  help  and our prayer.  And  so. under the  Patronage  of Our Lady of Lebanon.  we  invite  you  to the  Maronite  Cathedral.  which bears  her  name.  to  pray  for  the  Lebanese  people  and  for  the  vision.  dream  and  hope  that  is Lebanon!

I hope to see you!

Sincerely yours in Christ,
+ Gregory John Mansour


Prayer text: http://ololc.org/doc/prayer-for-lebanon-ramsho.pdf

https://www.stmaron.org/press-releases/solemn-act-of-consecration-of-humanity-and-russia-and-ukraine-in-particular-to-the-immaculate-heart-of-mary

Pope Francis asks us to join in a solemn Act of Consecration of humanity, and Russia and Ukraine in particular, to the Immaculate Heart of Mary. The Holy Father himself will pray his solemn Act of Consecration in Rome at approximately 6:30pm (Rome), 12:30pm (Eastern time), March 25, 2022.

He asks us to join him in prayer in our churches, homes and places of prayer that day, Friday, March 25.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Matthew.

Sixth prayer -- Dec. 20: (modern)


Sixth oration -- Dec. 20: (classic)

O Word of God, Who comes
from the Mouth of God to be the
Life of all men; You Who became
Living Bread and was born in
Bethlehem, "The House of Bread",
to satisfy our hunger; We beseech
You, through Your Pure Nativity
and the intercession of Your
Mother and Saint Joseph, Your
Chosen One, to grant us a piercing
hunger for that Bread which is
Your Pure Body and Blood.  May
we ever approach Your altar and
receive Your Sacred Mysteries
with fitting preparation so that our
Communion may be for us
salvation and life everlasting.
Amen.

snippet.title: The Christmas Novena
snippet.description:
The Christmas Novena prayers can be found at http://ololc.org/doc/novena.pdf.
Cover art by Tony.

Fourth prayer -- Dec. 18: (modern)

O  Lord,  Wine  of  the  Virgins  and  Lily  of  Purity,  through 
your body all bodies are purified and all souls are clothed 
in chastity. By dwelling in the womb of your mother, you 
have  made  her  the  most  pure  and  glorious  of  all  virgins. 
We implore you, through your pure nativity and through 
the  intercession  of  your  mother  and  Saint  Joseph,  your 
chosen one, to make our souls and bodies chaste and our 
thoughts and actions pure, that we may serve you all the 
days of our lives. Amen.  



Fourth oration -- Dec. 18: (classic)

0 Wine of Virgins and Lily of Purity,
Who by a touch of Your hand heals the body and cleanses the soul;
Who by dwelling in the womb of Your Mother has made her the purest of the pure and most admirable among virgins;

We beseech You, through Your Pure Nativity
and through the intercession of Your Mother and Saint Joseph, Your Chosen One,
to grant us to be pure in soul and body and clean in act clean and thought,
that we may serve You with a clean heart and pure body all the days of our lives.

Amen
